  41. ‌  let add_parens_if_symbolic = function
  42.     | "" -> ""
  43.     | s ->
  44.        match s.[0] with
  45.        | 'a'..'z' | 'A'..'Z' | '_' | '0'..'9' -> s
  46.        | _ -> "(" ^ s ^ ")"

  48. ‌  let dot ?(sep = ".") scopes s =
  49.     let s = add_parens_if_symbolic s in
  50.     match scopes with
  51.     | Empty -> s
  52.     | Cons {str; _} -> str ^ sep ^ s

  54. ‌  let enter_anonymous_function ~scopes =
  55.     let str = str_fun scopes in
  56.     Cons {item = Sc_anonymous_function; str; str_fun = str}

  58.   let enter_value_definition ~scopes id =
  59.     cons Sc_value_definition (dot scopes (Ident.name id))

  61.   let enter_module_definition ~scopes id =
  62.     cons Sc_module_definition (dot scopes (Ident.name id))

  64.   let enter_class_definition ~scopes id =

  67.   let enter_method_definition ~scopes (s : Asttypes.label) =

  137. ‌let item_from_location ~scopes loc =
  138.   let valid_endpos =
  139.     String.equal loc.loc_end.pos_fname loc.loc_start.pos_fname in
  140.   { dinfo_file = loc.loc_start.pos_fname;
  141.     dinfo_line = loc.loc_start.pos_lnum;
  142.     dinfo_char_start = loc.loc_start.pos_cnum - loc.loc_start.pos_bol;
  143.     dinfo_char_end =
  144.       if valid_endpos
  145.       then loc.loc_end.pos_cnum - loc.loc_start.pos_bol
  146.       else loc.loc_start.pos_cnum - loc.loc_start.pos_bol;
  147.     dinfo_start_bol = loc.loc_start.pos_bol;
  148.     dinfo_end_bol =
  149.       if valid_endpos then loc.loc_end.pos_bol
  150.       else loc.loc_start.pos_bol;
  151.     dinfo_end_line =
  152.       if valid_endpos then loc.loc_end.pos_lnum
  153.       else loc.loc_start.pos_lnum;
  154.     dinfo_scopes = scopes
  155.   }

  157. let from_location = function
  158.   | Scoped_location.Loc_unknown -> []
  159.   | Scoped_location.Loc_known {scopes; loc} ->
  160.     assert (not (Location.is_none loc));
  161.     [item_from_location ~scopes loc]

  163. let to_location = function
  164.   | [] -> Location.none
  165.   | d :: _ ->
  166.     let loc_start =
  167.       { pos_fname = d.dinfo_file;
  168.         pos_lnum = d.dinfo_line;
  169.         pos_bol = d.dinfo_start_bol;
  170.         pos_cnum = d.dinfo_start_bol + d.dinfo_char_start;
  171.       } in
  172. ‌    let loc_end =
  173.       { pos_fname = d.dinfo_file;
  174.         pos_lnum = d.dinfo_end_line;
  175.         pos_bol = d.dinfo_end_bol;
  176.         pos_cnum = d.dinfo_start_bol + d.dinfo_char_end;
  177.       } in
  178.     { loc_ghost = false; loc_start; loc_end; }

  188. ‌let compare dbg1 dbg2 =
  189.   let rec loop ds1 ds2 =
  190.     match ds1, ds2 with
  191.     | [], [] -> 0
  192.     | _ :: _, [] -> 1
  193.     | [], _ :: _ -> -1
  194.     | d1 :: ds1, d2 :: ds2 ->
  195.       let c = String.compare d1.dinfo_file d2.dinfo_file in
  196.       if c <> 0 then c else
  197.       let c = compare d1.dinfo_line d2.dinfo_line in
  198.       if c <> 0 then c else
  199.       let c = compare d1.dinfo_char_end d2.dinfo_char_end in
  200.       if c <> 0 then c else
  201.       let c = compare d1.dinfo_char_start d2.dinfo_char_start in
  202.       if c <> 0 then c else
  203.       let c = compare d1.dinfo_start_bol d2.dinfo_start_bol in
  204.       if c <> 0 then c else
  205.       let c = compare d1.dinfo_end_bol d2.dinfo_end_bol in
  206.       if c <> 0 then c else
  207.       let c = compare d1.dinfo_end_line d2.dinfo_end_line in
  208.       if c <> 0 then c else
  209.       loop ds1 ds2
  210.   in
  211.   loop (List.rev dbg1) (List.rev dbg2)

  213. ‌let hash t =

  216. let rec print_compact ppf t =
  217.   let print_item item =
  218.     Format.fprintf ppf "%a:%i"
  219.       Location.print_filename item.dinfo_file
  220.       item.dinfo_line;
  221.     if item.dinfo_char_start >= 0 then begin
  222.       Format.fprintf ppf ",%i--%i" item.dinfo_char_start item.dinfo_char_end
  223.     end
  224.   in
  225.   match t with
  226.   | [] -> ()
  227.   | [item] -> print_item item
  228.   | item::t ->
  229.     print_item item;
  230.     Format.fprintf ppf ";";
  231.     print_compact ppf t
